page.title: 11Birds of Lowna and the Moors
page.content: In the past year the following birds have been seen:-owls(tawny,little and barn)collared and stock dove,woodcock, black-headed gull,snipe,curlew,lapwing golden plover,moorhen,pheasant,kestrel grouse,merlin,hen harrier,sparrow hawk mallard,heron,rook,crow,jackdaw,magpie jay,starling,house sparrow,redpol, linnet,goldfinch,bullfinch,greenfinch, chaffinch,reed bunting,yellowhammer, treecreeper,dipper,nuthatch,tits(marsh willow,great,blue,long-tailed),dunnock thrush(song,mistle),blackbird,robin goldcrest,pied wagtail,meadow pipit, skylark,woodpecker(great spotted, green) and kingfisher.Summer visitors: whinchat,flycatcher(spotted,pied)swift warbler(garden,willow),chiffchaff,tree pipit,blackcap,whitethroat,greywagtail swallow,house martin,nightjar,cuckoo, ring ouzel,wheatear.Winter visitors:- brambling,redwing and fieldfare.
